ExamTopics practice questions were only accessible by scrolling to the bottom of the Course Modules page — no direct entry point existed.

## Changes

- **`index.html`** — Added "ExamTopics Q&A" nav item (clipboard-list icon) to the sidebar, positioned between Exam Readiness and Resources
- **`modules.js`** — Registered a standalone `examtopics` route that renders the ExamTopics card with its own page header, reusing the existing `renderExamTopicsCard()` function

```js
Router.register('examtopics', () => {
  return `<div class="fade-in">
    <div class="page-header">
      <div class="page-title"><i class="fas fa-clipboard-list blue"></i> ExamTopics Q&amp;A</div>
      <div class="page-subtitle">Real exam-style practice questions sourced from the community</div>
    </div>
    ${renderExamTopicsCard()}
  </div>`;
});
```

The questions remain embedded at the bottom of Course Modules as well — no existing behaviour removed.
